        </td><td colspan="1" rowspan="1">
          Typically 10-20 years
        </td></tr></tbody></table><div data-unit-credible="simple-cta,mortgage,compare-rates" class="credible"></div><h2><a name="faq" id="faq"></a>FAQ</h2><h3>What is a rate lock?</h3><p>Interest rates on mortgages fluctuate all the time, but a rate lock allows you to lock in your current rate for a set amount of time. This ensures you get the rate you want as you complete the <a href="http://www.foxbusiness.com/personal-finance/first-time-homebuyer-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><u>homebuying process</u></a>.</p><h3>What are mortgage points?</h3><p>Mortgage points are a type of prepaid interest that you can pay upfront &#x2014; often as part of your closing costs &#x2014; for a lower overall interest rate. This can lower your APR and monthly payments.&#xA0;</p><div class="ad-container mobile ad-h-250 ad-w-300 ad-placeholder-load"><div data-iu="ban10" id="mobile-mw-ad-ban10" class="ad gam inline"></div></div><h3>What are closing costs?</h3><p>Closing costs are the fees you, as the buyer, need to pay before getting a loan. Common fees include attorney fees, home appraisal fees, <a href="http://www.foxbusiness.com/money/mortgage-origination-fees-what-are-how-to-avoid" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><u>origination fees</u></a>, and application fees.</p><p>If you&#x2019;re trying to find the right mortgage rate, consider using Credible. You can <a href="https://www.credible.com/mortgage/rates/landing?utm_source=fox&amp;utm_medium=partner_link&amp;utm_campaign=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftodays-mortgage-rates-may-2-2024" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">use Credible&apos;s free online tool</a> to easily compare multiple lenders and see prequalified rates in just a few minutes.</p></div> <footer class="article-footer"><!----> <!----> <div class="partners"><div class="partner geo-item"><div data-uid="fbr-ar-21" class="vendor-unit "></div></div> <div class="partner geo-item"><div data-uid="fbr-ar-22" class="vendor-unit "></div></div